 that she is playing [[Roxie Hart]] in the musical ''[[Chicago (musical)|Chicago]]'' on [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/ChicagoMusical/status/1176877794346897409|title=It'd be criminal to miss @erikajayne as Roxie Hart. Catch her on Broadway beginning January 6.pic.twitter.com/RKt7TAyZ1D|last=Musical|first=Chicago The|date=2019-09-25|website=@ChicagoMusical|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref><ref name=\":18\">{{Cite web|url=https://nypost.com/2019/09/25/rhobh-star-erika-jayne-to-make-broadway-debut-in-chicago/|title=\u2018RHOBH\u2019 star Erika Jayne to make Broadway debut in \u2018Chicago\u2019|last=Bailey-Millado|first=Rob|date=2019-09-25|website=New York Post|language=en|access-date=2020-03-11}}</ref> Her performances were originally set to run from January 6 to March 29, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/theater/rhobh-erika-jayne-chicago-the-musical-roxie-hart/|title=From Beverly Hills to Broadway! RHOBH's Erika Jayne to Play Roxie Hart in Chicago the Musical|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.papermag.com/erika-jayne-chicago-2640620336.html|title=Erika Jayne Is Making Her Broadway Debut|date=2019-09-26|website=PAPER|language=en|access-date=2019-09-26}}</ref><ref name=\":11\" /> On March 12, 2020, she announced that her Broadway production has ended weeks early due to [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Coronavirus]] shutdown.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/broadway-stars-react-theater-shutdowns-232443181.html|title=Broadway Stars React To Theater Shutdowns With Well Wishes & Good Humor: \"Welp, It\u2019s Been Real Y\u2019all\" Tweets David Alan Grier|website=yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> [[Governor of New York|New York Governor]] [[Andrew Cuomo]] and Broadway League President Charlotte St. Martin announced that all Broadway performances have been canceled until April 12, 2020 due to concerns about the Coronavirus.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://people.com/theater/erika-jayne-forced-to-end-her-broadway-chicago-run-weeks-early-due-to-coronavirus-shutdown/|title=Erika Jayne Forced to End Her Broadway Chicago Run Weeks Early Due to Coronavirus Shutdown|website=PEOPLE.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==Public image==\nFashion has also been a part of Jayne's music career and image.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bravotv.com/the-real-housewives-of-beverly-hills/lookbook/erika-girardi-sheer-jumpsuit-for-cr-fashion-book|title=Erika Girardi Can Work a See-Through Bodysuit Like No Other|date=2018-04-13|work=Bravo TV Official Site|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref> She has frequently worn clothes designed by [[Gucci]], [[Moschino]], [[Versace]], [[Balmain (fashion house)|Balmain]], and [[Alexander McQueen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bigblondehair.com/character/erika-girardi/|title=Erika GIrardi {{!}} You Source for Real Housewives Fashion and Style|website=bigblondehair.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.brit.co/erika-jayne-beauty-hair-wardrobe-costs/|title=Erika Jayne Spends $40,000 Each Month on Her Glam Look|access-date=2018-06-23|language=en-us}}</ref> Tyler McCall of Fashionista.com called her \"debatably the most stylish cast member of any ''Real Housewives'' franchise.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://fashionista.com/2017/04/erika-jayne-real-housewives-style-clothes|title=Erika Jayne: How I Shop|work=Fashionista|access-date=2018-06-23|language=en}}</ref> In 2018, she was the first star of ''[[The Real Housewives]]'' media franchise to attend the [[Council of Fashion Designers of America|CFDA Fashion Awards]] and was placed on several \"best-dressed lists\" after her appearance on the award show''.''<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/style/cfda-awards-2018-erika-jayne-suit/?xid=socialflow_twitter_peoplemag|title=Erika Jayne Is the 'First Housewife' to Ever Attend the CFDA Awards: See Her 'Sophistica